Author: Godballz#9524
Content: Off topic question: Can a DeX or even an exchange have a coin that recognizes many types of different crypto addresses and automatically utilizes stored crypto assets to convert them in real time for trade across platforms? Basically a coin that can become a btc or vrsc or eth etc upon transfer since exchanges carry large volumes of each coin anyway and already track conversion rates. Of course it couldnt borrow escrow or orders so it'd have to be based off fees stored in accounts. Jw if this can exist or if it already does as I'd imagine it'd improve crypto usability and ease of use and in turn, adoption

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content:
not clear on the question exactly.
you saying a DEX which can auto trade the portfolio of a person, and with a choice of which is the main trading coin for that portfolio, like if user wants to have more liquidity in BTC then the goal of portfolio is it get more of BTC by auto trading etc?

As I understand it it already exists in the existing version 1.0 of `marketmaker` API, and is also GUIed in BarterDEX GUI under advanced UI interface.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content:
in BarterDEX, user can trade ANY coin to ANY coin, and also set the percentage of the coins to auto trade based on either price range or margin range.
It's the perfect tool for market makers
